Turkana elders in Laikipia want the national government to expedite the issuance of identity cards to the community.In a petition filed in the National Assembly, the residents, through Turkana North MP Christopher Nakuleu, want the government to stop the &ldquo;biased vetting process&rdquo;.&ldquo;The Constitution prohibits all forms of direct or indirect discrimination against members of any community,&rdquo; the petition says.The petitioners want Interior Cabinet Secretary Joseph Nkaissery to revoke any order directing the &ldquo;tedious&rdquo; vetting by the offices responsible for registration of persons in the county.&ldquo;The lengthy vetting process has deprived the community of their right to choose their leaders,&rdquo; it reads.The petition is before the Administration and National Security Committee of the National Assembly chaired by Tiaty MP Asman Kamama. The committee is yet to visit Laikipia to investigate the issue.The county is inhabited by the Samburu, Maasai, Pokot, Kikuyu, Kalenjin, Somali, Borana and Meru.